# Core standards

- Keep changes small and consistent with existing patterns in `src/`.
- Use `pnpm` for all package management commands.
- Prefer readability over cleverness; avoid premature abstraction.

## Styling

- Do **not** use inline styles (`style={{ ... }}`) in JSX.
- Prefer colocated component styles (see component structure rule) or shared styles in `src/styles/`.

## TypeScript + linting

- TypeScript must remain `strict: true`.
- Do not add `// eslint-disable` / `/* eslint-disable */` comments. Fix the underlying issue instead.
- Avoid `any`. If you must use it, isolate it behind a well-typed boundary and document why in the PR/commit message (not as `eslint-disable`).

